author: The Emporia Gazette
title: CGHS VB posts 1-2 record at home invite
text:
CGHS VB posts 1-2 record at home invite The Emporia Gazette   0 comments 
Council Grove’s volleyball team went 1-2 in pool play at its home invitational Saturday while Northern Heights came out winless in the other pool. Abilene won the tournament, posting a 5-0 record. 
The Braves’ lone win came against St. Mary’s, 25-13, 26-24. Council Grove opened with a 20-25, 15-25 loss to Clay Center and dropped another two-set match to Clearwater (14-25, 24-26), keeping the Braves from advancing to bracket play. 
Northern Heights lost to Abilene (4-25, 8-25), Sacred Heart (21-25, 16-25) and Santa Fe Trail (13-25, 24-26). 
Council Grove’s record fell to 22-6 on the season while the Braves will put their undefeated (12-0) Flint Hills League record on the line Tuesday against Chase County.
